<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/02012019bakiessh2-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&amp;ssl=1" alt="Hacker who stole $500K by ‘SIM-swapping’ cuts plea deal" class="amp-wp-295b586"> An Ohio hacker charged with stealing $500,000 from the comfort of his mother’s home amid a 10-day hacking spree copped to just two felony charges in a plea deal Monday. Dawson Bakies, 21, managed to avoid the other 50 counts of identity theft and scheme to defraud he was facing — but he’ll have to fork over most of his electronics, according to the deal cut in Manhattan Criminal Court on Monday. Continue reading Hacker who stole $500K by ‘SIM-swapping’ cuts plea deal at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard